Most queries count entities in a simple relation to one named entity, i.e., the avg.\ query length is 6.40 words, with an average of 1.08 named entities per query. We found that 95% of the 322 queries returned non-empty answer types, with more than 200 unique phrases, for instance, sibling, movie, employee, nfl stadium, real estate agent, czech player. The queries spanned over 49 different relations.